00:15:43.130 --> 00:15:45.270
but he's still really
very much would like

00:15:45.270 --> 00:15:49.070
to bust after I show to Heap78.

00:15:49.070 --> 00:15:51.020
So he can't call with anything.

00:15:51.020 --> 00:15:53.600
With ace-4, I think that's
definitely good enough to call.

00:15:53.600 --> 00:15:56.870
But let's say they
have king-2 offsuit.

00:15:56.870 --> 00:15:59.560
I think that's the situation
I'd normally call if it was not

00:15:59.560 --> 00:16:01.000
a final table in a tournament.

00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:03.610
But at the final table,
where I'm not the shortest

00:16:03.610 --> 00:16:05.150
and there's someone
shorter than me,

00:16:05.150 --> 00:16:06.995
I would consider folding 10-2--

00:16:06.995 --> 00:16:14.740
sorry, king-2 offsuit here just
because of ICM essentially.

00:16:14.740 --> 00:16:17.760
All right, so the next hand--

00:16:17.760 --> 00:16:19.450
so the big blind busts.

00:16:19.450 --> 00:16:21.350
And then there's no
small blind in this hand,

00:16:21.350 --> 00:16:25.050
which is great because people
are less incentivized to steal.

00:16:25.050 --> 00:16:27.135
And indeed we get
our big blind back.

00:16:27.135 --> 00:16:28.010
AUDIENCE: That works.

00:16:28.010 --> 00:16:30.610
WILL MA: Very nice.

