00:17:32.790 --> 00:17:34.370
it actually seems
quite reasonable

00:17:34.370 --> 00:17:37.160
if you think about it
because for him, ace-queen

00:17:37.160 --> 00:17:38.840
is a great hand
from this position.

00:17:38.840 --> 00:17:41.150
It's definitely
good enough where

00:17:41.150 --> 00:17:45.110
if it was between folding and
shoving for 23 big blinds,

00:17:45.110 --> 00:17:47.900
you would definitely rather
shove for 23 big blinds.

00:17:47.900 --> 00:17:51.520
So the main reason why normally
one would criticize his play

00:17:51.520 --> 00:17:54.950
is because why doesn't he just
raise small with ace-queen?

00:17:54.950 --> 00:17:57.610
Well, understandably,
he doesn't really

00:17:57.610 --> 00:18:01.160
want to incentivize me
to reraise or Panpancrisy

00:18:01.160 --> 00:18:01.910
to make a reraise.

00:18:01.910 --> 00:18:04.790
He essentially wants
to minimize the chances

00:18:04.790 --> 00:18:08.160
that he has to play for
his stack in this hand.

00:18:08.160 --> 00:18:10.520
And the way he does that is
essentially by going all in.

00:18:13.730 --> 00:18:16.310
Looking at back at it, I
think his play is fine.

00:18:16.310 --> 00:18:18.790
The only weakness of
his play, I think,

00:18:18.790 --> 00:18:23.120
is it is a bit predictable what
his hand is in this situation

00:18:23.120 --> 00:18:26.720
because I think if he had a
hand as good as pocket aces,

00:18:26.720 --> 00:18:28.227
then he shouldn't be doing this.

00:18:28.227 --> 00:18:30.560
He should just be raising
small because it's good enough

00:18:30.560 --> 00:18:35.130
where he's happy getting it
in against me or Panpancrisy.

00:18:35.130 --> 00:18:38.250
Whereas also if his
hand was slightly worse,

00:18:38.250 --> 00:18:40.370
like ace-jack offsuit I
think is a good example,

00:18:40.370 --> 00:18:44.150
I think ace-jack offsuit
is not strong enough

00:18:44.150 --> 00:18:45.550
to make this all-in play with.

00:18:45.550 --> 00:18:47.090
But you still want
to be raising.

00:18:47.090 --> 00:18:49.490
So I think there's a
small range of hands

00:18:49.490 --> 00:18:51.470
that you want to be making
this all-in play is.

00:18:51.470 --> 00:18:55.520
I think it's basically
exactly he's queen offsuit,

00:18:55.520 --> 00:18:58.040
may ace-king, maybe
ace-queen, ace-king.

00:18:58.040 --> 00:19:02.420
And then middle pairs, let's
say between like pocket 8s

00:19:02.420 --> 00:19:04.760
and pocket 10s or something.

00:19:04.760 --> 00:19:06.740
So the only downside
of this play I think

00:19:06.740 --> 00:19:09.560
is essentially his range
here is very predictable it's

00:19:09.560 --> 00:19:13.710
going to be ace-jack suited
plus ace-queen and pocket 8s

00:19:13.710 --> 00:19:15.500
through 10s or
something like that.

00:19:15.500 --> 00:19:18.530
But nonetheless, I think,
because it's a final table,

00:19:18.530 --> 00:19:21.401
because of ICM, it's fine.

00:19:21.401 --> 00:19:22.400
He gets unlucky, though.

00:19:22.400 --> 00:19:23.954
He runs into queens.

00:19:23.954 --> 00:19:25.370
All right, here
we've got to walk.

00:19:28.240 --> 00:19:30.400
OK, so let's see this hand.

