00:45:22.620 --> 00:45:26.700
about this theory of satellites
and going all in first.

00:45:26.700 --> 00:45:30.435
So in game theory, this is
called the traffic intersection

00:45:30.435 --> 00:45:31.230
game.

00:45:31.230 --> 00:45:34.200
So ICM does not
say, play tighter.

00:45:34.200 --> 00:45:37.140
It allows you to play looser
if you can go all in first.

00:45:37.140 --> 00:45:39.060
So this is where
I actually think

00:45:39.060 --> 00:45:41.430
it's very interesting
because in satellites, you

00:45:41.430 --> 00:45:42.870
want to be under the gun.

00:45:42.870 --> 00:45:45.530
So normally in poker, that's the
worst position because you've

00:45:45.530 --> 00:45:46.770
got to act first.

00:45:46.770 --> 00:45:49.260
Everyone else gets
to act after you.

00:45:49.260 --> 00:45:51.420
But in satellites,
basically you just

00:45:51.420 --> 00:45:54.600
want to be the first person to
be able to threaten, say, look,

00:45:54.600 --> 00:45:55.890
I'm putting all my chips in.

00:45:55.890 --> 00:45:58.320
You pretty much have to fold.

00:45:58.320 --> 00:46:01.260
So in satellites, let's
say there's 11 people left,

00:46:01.260 --> 00:46:02.780
and 10 people get a seat.

00:46:02.780 --> 00:46:04.680
If you go on, no
one can call you

00:46:04.680 --> 00:46:08.760
even if they have aces
because to call you,

00:46:08.760 --> 00:46:10.920
they essentially need
to be more than 10/11

00:46:10.920 --> 00:46:12.854
sure that they're
going to win the hand.

00:46:12.854 --> 00:46:14.270
And even if they
have pocket aces,

00:46:14.270 --> 00:46:16.410
they're not going to be
10/11 sure that they're

00:46:16.410 --> 00:46:17.460
going to win the hand.

00:46:17.460 --> 00:46:22.880
So basically going all in
first is very, very good.

00:46:22.880 --> 00:46:24.930
So it's called the
traffic interception game

00:46:24.930 --> 00:46:26.880
because you can imagine
the situation where

00:46:26.880 --> 00:46:30.420
there's two cars trying to pass
each other at an intersection.

00:46:30.420 --> 00:46:34.200
And you want to save
time, get there first.

00:46:34.200 --> 00:46:37.140
But you're worried that
the other guy might crash.

00:46:37.140 --> 00:46:38.932
Both players really
want to avoid disaster,

00:46:38.932 --> 00:46:40.681
but both players really
want to be the guy

00:46:40.681 --> 00:46:41.710
to get through first.

00:46:41.710 --> 00:46:44.850
Well, if you can act first, and
if you just tell the guy, look,

00:46:44.850 --> 00:46:46.650
I'm closing my eyes.

00:46:46.650 --> 00:46:47.640
I'm tying up my hands.

00:46:47.640 --> 00:46:50.110
I cannot stop my car, OK?

00:46:50.110 --> 00:46:52.770
I'm just going to go through
the intersection no matter what.

00:46:52.770 --> 00:46:55.050
If you're the first person
to be able to do this, then

00:46:55.050 --> 00:46:56.880
the other guy, he's
like, OK, I guess

00:46:56.880 --> 00:46:59.250
I've got to stop my car
now and let you go first.

00:46:59.250 --> 00:47:00.960
That's essentially
what it's like.

00:47:00.960 --> 00:47:03.870
If you're the first person to go
all in and you've already said,

00:47:03.870 --> 00:47:05.700
look, I'm all in,
and there's nothing

00:47:05.700 --> 00:47:08.599
I can do to take my chips back,
then the other guy is like,

00:47:08.599 --> 00:47:09.890
all right, I guess I'll follow.

00:47:09.890 --> 00:47:11.220
And you can win the blinds.

00:47:11.220 --> 00:47:13.290
So it's sort of how it works.

00:47:13.290 --> 00:47:15.520
Of course, some opponents
are not rational.

00:47:15.520 --> 00:47:16.952
If you do this
enough times, they

00:47:16.952 --> 00:47:18.690
might be like, OK, screw this.

00:47:18.690 --> 00:47:22.220
I'm just going to kill
this guy and speed up.

00:47:22.220 --> 00:47:25.481
So it's a bit weird, and in
practice, this happens a lot,

00:47:25.481 --> 00:47:25.980
